  <thing id="io5CWtchVan" name="Witchlight Vane" description="This rod is ornately decorated, including butterfly wings at its top and red glass incorporated throughout its length.\n\n{b}Magic Weapon.{/b} When wielded by the creature it&apos;s attuned to, the vane can be used as a magic mace with a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls. The vane deals an additional 1d8 radiant damage on a hit.\n\n{b}Sense Mood.{/b} While the vane is within the bounds of the Witchlight Carnival, it can sense the mood of every creature in the carnival with an Intelligence of 4 or higher. The creature attuned to the vane can use an action to pinpoint the location of the happiest creature in the carnival.\nThe butterfly shape at the top of the vane slowly spins clockwise when the general mood of the carnival is high. Conversely, if spirits are low, the top of the vane spins slowly counterclockwise.\n\n{b}Sentience.{/b} The vane is a sentient, chaotic good wondrous item with Intelligence 11, Wisdom 14, and Charisma 14. It has hearing and normal vision out to 30 feet, and it communicates through emotions, trasmitted to the creature attuned to it. Its true purpose is to ensure the patrons of the carnival are having a good time.\n\n{b}Additional Properties.{/b} The vane has these additional properties:\n• The creature holding the vane is vulnerable to lightning damage.\n• The creature attuned to the vane is immune to the blinded, deafened, petrified, and stunned conditions.\n• While carrying the vane, the creature attuned to it can use an action to cast one of these spells without needing any spell components and using Charisma as the spellcasting ability: {i}dancing lights{/i}, {i}polymorph{/i}, and {i}ray of frost{/i}. After the vane is used to cast {i}polymorph{/i}, roll a d8; on a roll of 3 or 8, the vane can&apos;t be used to cast this spell again until the following dawn." compset="Wondrous">
