  <thing id="io5CWtchWat" name="Witchlight Watch" description="This ornate pocket watch is fastened to the end of a gold chain. When opened, it has a faint golden glow and softly ticks, a sound that is only audible to the creature holding it. The watchface is an ornate image of the carnival, with a circle of stones that tell the time.\n\n{b}Carnival Setup and Takedown.{/b} The creature attuned to the watch can use an action to initiate the packing up or the unpacking of the carnival, provided the creature and the carnival are on the same plane of existence. Over the course of an hour, all objects that are part of the carnival are magically moved around until everything is packed up and ready for travel, or unpacked and assembled. The watch does not affect creatures, which can move about freely and safely while the setup/unpacking process occurs. Once the process starts, it can&apos;t be halted until it is finished. Once the watch has been used to pack up or unpack the carnival, this property cannot be used again until 8 hours have passed.\n\n{b}Additional Properties.{/b} The pocket watch has these additional properties:\n• While carrying the watch, the creature attuned to it can use an action to cast one of the following spells, needing no spell components and using Intelligence as the spellcasting ability: {i}fire bolt{/i}, {i}invisibility{/i}, and {i}message{/i}. After the watch&apos;s {i}invisibility{/i} spell is cast, roll a d8; on a roll of 3 or 8, the watch can&apos;t be used to cast this spell again until the following dawn.\n• The creature attuned to the watch gains 30 pounds. This extra weight vanishes when the attunement ends.\n• The creature attuned to the watch must eat and drink eight times the normal amount every day." compset="Wondrous">
